Dear {{PatientPreferredName}}:

During the consultation, it is often impossible to talk about everything, either for lack of time or something slipping my mind.  At this time, I would like to reinforce and re-emphasize points that may not have been discussed during your consultation visit.

My staff is an integral part of this practice since I would be unable to accomplish all of the various technical tasks without their considerable help.  You may expect to see them performing many services for the patients as I am not able to be in all areas at once.  Should you have questions during treatment, please feel free to speak to either me or my staff.  They are very competent to handle most problems, and you will find them easily accessible.

Orthodontic treatment cannot be completed without the total cooperation of the patient.  The areas which we are most concerned about are cleaning the teeth, wearing elastics, following instructions for headgear, and not abusing the braces. One of the orthodontist's greatest joys is a happy, cooperative patient, and an orthodontist's deepest despair is the occasional patient who “couldn’t care less” about the whole project.

Again, if you should have questions concerning your treatment, please feel free to seek me out or call.  I welcome your interest.

For the most part I expect the next couple of years to be a lot of fun for all of us, and look forward to getting to know you better.

Sincerely,


{{DoctorSignature}}

                {{TodayDate}}


