Dear {{PatientPreferredName}}:


When you were in today, it was evident that our instructions for proper teeth cleaning are not being followed.  As a result, you have an infection of the gum tissue that could spread and cause a loss of the bone which surrounds the teeth.

The only reason for this infection is neglect on your part.  When food is not removed around the teeth and gums, bacteria use the food to produce toxic waste which causes bone destruction.

Please take this situation seriously.  You could suffer irreparable damage unless every effort is made to correct the problem.  One of my assistants who is specially trained to solve oral hygiene problems will be seeing you until this problem is resolved.

Treatment must be discontinued until the infection eliminated by adequate oral hygiene.  We cannot move teeth into an area of infection.  Please work closely with my staff to resolve this serious problem.

Sincerely,



{{DoctorSignature}}
